# `README.yml` — format and authoring

## Language

All generated text (descriptions, feature titles, notes, table cells) must be written in **English**.

## Scope

Shared across many Terraform module repos. **Never** embed another project's org, repo name, registry address, or module story — derive identifiers only from the module tree being edited (`git` remote, `source` in examples, or neutral placeholders). **Inputs:** `*.tf` under the module root (including `examples/**` when present) and this file only — do **not** assume a pre-existing `README.yml`.

---

## Top-level shape (order)

```yaml
module_name: "…"
module_description: |
  …
module_badges:
  - url: "…"
    image: "…"
    alt: "…"
quick_start: |
  ```hcl
  <prefix>_parameters = { … }
  ```
features:
  - icon: "…"
    title: "…"
    short_description: "…"
    long_description: |
      …
    examples:
      - title: "…"
        code: |
          ```hcl
          …
          ```
important_notes: |
  - …
input_table: |
  | … |
```

Only these seven top-level keys. Multiline fields use `|`. UTF-8, 2-space indent.

---

## Section rules

### `module_name`
Single-line header title; no version numbers. Format: `"Terraform <Title-Cased module segment> Module"`, derived from the repo name / GitHub concern name. Example: `terraform-github-wrapper-organization` → `"Terraform Organization Module"`.

### `module_description`
Marketing + scope (what / why). No resource names, internal flags, or step-by-step behavior. One strong line or `|` multiline when two short paragraphs are justified.

### `module_badges`
`url` / `image` / `alt` per item. `image` = Shields-style `style=for-the-badge`. Default triple when URLs are known:
1. Latest release — `url`: `https://github.com/<org>/<repo>/releases/latest` | `image`: `img.shields.io/github/v/release/<org>/<repo>.svg?style=for-the-badge`
2. Last commit — `url: ""` | `image`: `img.shields.io/github/last-commit/<org>/<repo>.svg?style=for-the-badge`
3. Terraform Registry — always include. Derive from the GitHub remote using the convention `terraform-<provider>-<module-name>`: `url`: `https://registry.terraform.io/modules/<org>/<module-name>/<provider>` | `image`: `https://img.shields.io/badge/Terraform-Registry-7B42BC?style=for-the-badge&logo=terraform&logoColor=white`. Example: remote `gocloudLa/terraform-github-wrapper-organization` → org=`gocloudLa`, provider=`github`, module=`wrapper-organization`.

Use `git` remote to resolve `<org>/<repo>`.

### `quick_start`
**Exactly one** ```` ```hcl ```` fence containing only `<root_*_parameters_name> = { … }`. No `module`, `provider`, `terraform`, or other root blocks. When `examples/**` exists, mirror the richest file's key order, spacing, and comment wording — do not rename or reorder for style. Use `#` comment lines inside the map for optional overrides.

For single-resource wrappers gated by `enable_<service>`, include `enable_<service> = true` in the quick start when the example does.

### `features`
- `icon` = single Unicode emoji. Each item requires `icon`, `title`, `short_description`, `long_description` (pipe), `examples` (list).
- Each `examples[]` entry: `title` + `code` (pipe) with its own closed ```` ```hcl ```` fence; prefer `…_parameters = { … }` only.
- Mirror `examples/` grouping — if one file shows memberships + webhooks together, prefer one `feature` with two `examples` rather than splitting.
- `long_description` may reference provider resource types (`github_*`) when it clarifies multi-apply flows — concise prose, not a schema dump.
- One scenario per feature; use `# TBD` skeletons and note in `long_description` when a runnable example is missing. Use `examples: []` only when genuinely absent.

### `important_notes`
Warnings only: apply order across wrappers (org → team → repository), provider `owner` requirements, membership prerequisites, secret handling, destroy pitfalls. Optional severity emoji (`⚠️` / `ℹ️` / `🔒`) + **Bold label:** on the opening line. Keep few, sharp bullets — omit anything that merely repeats `input_table` mechanics.

### `input_table`
Pipe rows only — **omit header row and `| --- |` separator**. Column order: key | description | type | default | required (`yes` / `no` / `—`).

**Scope:** document only the keys that live *inside* the `*_parameters` map (or each map entry for `for_each` wrappers) — i.e. the attributes a user sets under `*_parameters = { … }` / `"name" = { … }`. Do **not** add rows for the top-level module variables themselves (`metadata`, `<service>_parameters`, `<service>_defaults`, etc.).

Row order: enable/identity keys → flags → resource IDs / names → option maps → nested lists. Defaults: prefer `null`, `{}`, booleans matching `variables.tf`/`try()`; use `—` only when no default applies.

---

## Authoring workflow

1. `variables.tf` → `*_parameters` name + full key set → drives `quick_start` and `input_table`.
2. `main.tf` / `locals.tf` → optional keys, `try` chains, nesting → drives `features`.
3. Best `examples/…/main.tf` → authoritative key order, comments, multi-step patterns.
4. Write: `module_description` → `quick_start` → `features` → `important_notes` → `input_table`.
5. Validate YAML and every ```` ```hcl ```` fence closes.
